    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out at this risk level. The CFD model demonstrates sufficient credibility to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The primary validation result shows NRMSE of 8.3% on the RH index across all five CPB operating points, satisfying the 15% acceptance criterion. The supplementary HemoLab VAD dataset cross-check provides additional confidence through geometric and flow-rate overlap with the COU. The modelling team is satisfied that the evidence base supports the regulatory claim that RH < 1 at worst-case conditions.",
